Meaning of Symbols in the Diagram

| Symbol          | Meaning                                                                                                                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **œÉ (Sigmoid)** | Controls information flow (0 = block, 1 = allow). Used in Forget, Input, and Output Gates.                               |
| **tanh**        | Creates and scales memory values between **‚àí1 and +1**. Used for candidate memory and before producing the hidden state. |
| **√ó**           | Element-wise multiplication. Filters information according to the gate values.                                           |
| **+**           | Element-wise addition. Combines retained old memory with new candidate memory.                                           |


